<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<UserControl
    x:Class="tOrder.UI.InfoContentC"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    xmlns:local="using:tOrder.UI"
    xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
    xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
    mc:Ignorable="d">

    <Grid>
        <!-- 
        
Title: 
    Add “InfoContent” tab group to Capacity Unit Dashboard (5 tabs + head selector)

Summary:
    Create a new “InfoContent” section under CapacityUnitDashboard with a tab head (InfoTabsHeadC) and five tab content views. The tab selection is controlled by the parent TabSelectorView via a DP SelectedTab on InfoContentC. The head control emits TabChanged but final selection is set by the parent.
    
    Details:
    
    Add enum InfoTabKey { ProductionOrder, Shift, InboundContainers, OutboundContainers, ContainersForProcessing }.
    
    Implement InfoTabsHeadC (tabselector_head clone) with 5 buttons and SelectedTab DP + TabChanged event.
    
    Extend InfoContentC with SelectedTab DP. Render tab content via ContentPresenters and a simple TabToVisibilityConverter.
    
    Create 5 placeholder views in CapacityUnitDashboard/InfoContent/TabContent/:
    
    ProductionOrderView
    
    ShiftView
    
    InboundContainersView
    
    OutboundContainersView
    
    ContainersForProcessingView
    
    Parent TabSelectorView is responsible for setting InfoContentC.SelectedTab (centralized ShowTabContent logic).
    
    No business logic yet; data bindings will be wired in subsequent tasks.
    
    Acceptance Criteria:
    
    Clicking each tab in InfoTabsHeadC switches the displayed view when SelectedTab is set by the parent or via the head’s event.
    
    All files compile; placeholder headings are visible.
    
    SelectedTab defaults to ProductionOrder.

-->



    </Grid>
</UserControl>
